.TH Prepare-WebhookDeployment 1 "November 2025" "docker-webhook" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
Prepare-WebhookDeployment \- generate environment file, certificate request, and Docker Compose YAML for a location
.SH SYNOPSIS
Prepare-WebhookDeployment [OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Generates a webhook environment file (webhook-LOCATION.env), certificate request (certificate-request.conf), and a Docker Compose YAML file (webhook-LOCATION.yaml) for the specified LOCATION. Places the certificate request in webhook.config/LOCATION/ssl-certificates/ and the other files in the workspace root.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --env-file <file>
Load environment variables from a file. Variables in the file override defaults.
.TP
.B --location <location>
Set the location name (e.g., us-wa). Required.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show usage information and exit.
.PP
Other configuration values (country code, organization, etc.) are set via
environment variables or use default values.
.SH USAGE
.RS
.nf
\fBLOCATION=us-wa ./bin/Prepare-WebhookDeployment --location us-wa\fR
.fi
